    "reasoning": "Step 1: Compute d = lcm(23,22,10) - 2528. Since 23 is prime, 22=2*11, 10=2*5, lcm(22,10)=110, lcm(23,110)=2530, so d=2530-2528=2.\nStep 2: Solve 8 a^a b^b = 27 a^b b^a for positive integers a,b. Rewrite as 8 a^{a-b} b^{b-a}=27 => 8 (a/b)^{a-b}=27 => (a/b)^{a-b}=27/8=(3/2)^3. Let a/b = r, so r^{a-b}=(3/2)^3. Assuming a>b (by symmetry), set a/b=3/2 and a-b=3, giving a=9, b=6. Alternatively, parameterize with a=3^m t, b=2^m t, then equation becomes (3/2)^{m(3^m-2^m)t}=(3/2)^3, so m(3^m-2^m)t=3. For m=1, (3^1-2^1)=1, so t=3, giving a=9, b=6. Other m give non-integer t. So the positive integer solutions are (a,b)=(9,6) and (6,9).\nStep 3: Compute a^d+b^d with d=2: 9^2+6^2=81+36=117.",
